FROM frequents A, frequents B
WHERE A.bar = 'James Joyce Pub'
AND B.bar = 'Satisfaction'
AND A.drinker = B.drinker;

column1:
SELECT DISTINCT f1.drinker
FROM frequents AS f1, frequents AS f2
WHERE f1.bar='James Joyce Pub' 
AND f2.bar='Satisfaction'
AND f1.drinker = f2.drinker;

--(d) Find the names of drinkers who frequent both James Joyce Pub and Satisfaction. 
select f1.drinker
from frequents f1, frequents f2
where f1.drinker = f2.drinker and f1.bar = 'James Joyce Pub' and f2.bar = 'Satisfaction';

SELECT DISTINCT f1.drinker
FROM Frequents AS f1, Frequents AS f2
WHERE f1.drinker = f2.drinker
AND f1.bar = 'James Joyce Pub'
AND f2.bar = 'Satisfaction';

SELECT A.drinker FROM Frequents A
INNER JOIN Frequents B
ON A.drinker = B.drinker AND
A.bar = 'James Joyce Pub' AND B.bar = 'Satisfaction';

SELECT drinker
FROM frequents
WHERE bar = 'James Joyce Pub'
INTERSECT 
SELECT drinker
FROM frequents
WHERE bar = 'Satisfaction';
SELECT drinker FROM Frequents WHERE bar = 'James Joyce Pub' INTERSECT SELECT drinker FROM Frequents WHERE bar = 'Satisfaction';

SELECT 
jdrinker AS drinker
FROM(
SELECT DISTINCT
*
FROM
(SELECT DISTINCT
drinker AS jdrinker
FROM
Frequents
WHERE
bar = 'James Joyce Pub' ) AS JJP
JOIN
(SELECT DISTINCT
drinker as sdrinker
FROM
Frequents
WHERE
bar = 'Satisfaction' ) AS Satis
ON
JJP.jdrinker = Satis.sdrinker) VAMOS
;

SELECT Frequents.drinker
FROM Frequents
WHERE Frequents.bar = 'Satisfaction'
INTERSECT
SELECT Frequents.drinker
FROM Frequents
WHERE Frequents.bar = 'James Joyce Pub';

SELECT T.drinker
FROM (SELECT drinker FROM Frequents
      WHERE bar = 'James Joyce Pub')
      AS T,
     (SELECT drinker FROM Frequents
      WHERE bar = 'Satisfaction')
      AS R
WHERE T.drinker = R.drinker;
SELECT Frequents.drinker FROM Frequents WHERE Frequents.bar='James Joyce Pub' INTERSECT SELECT Frequents.drinker FROM Frequents WHERE Frequents.bar='Satisfaction';

SELECT Frequents.drinker FROM Frequents, Frequents AS Frequents2
WHERE Frequents.bar = 'James Joyce Pub'
AND Frequents2.bar = 'Satisfaction'
AND Frequents.drinker = Frequents2.drinker;
SELECT DISTINCT Drinker.name FROM Drinker, Frequents f1, Frequents f2 WHERE f1.bar = 'James Joyce Pub' AND f2.bar = 'Satisfaction' AND Drinker.name = f1.drinker AND Drinker.name = f2.drinker;

WHERE frequents.bar = 'James Joyce Pub')

(SELECT DISTINCT F.drinker FROM Frequents AS F WHERE F.bar LIKE '%James Joyce Pub%') INTERSECT (SELECT DISTINCT F.drinker FROM Frequents AS F WHERE F.bar LIKE 'Satisfaction%');

select distinct f1.drinker
from frequents f1
full join frequents f2
on f1.drinker = f2.drinker
where f1.bar = 'James Joyce Pub' and f2.bar = 'Satisfaction';
select distinct f1.drinker from frequents as f1, frequents as f2 where f1.drinker=f2.drinker and f1.bar='James Joyce Pub' and f2.bar='Satisfaction';

SELECT drinker
FROM frequents
WHERE bar = 'James Joyce Pub' OR bar = 'Satisfaction'
GROUP BY drinker
HAVING count(*) = 2
(SELECT drinker FROM Frequents WHERE frequents.bar='James Joyce Pub') INTERSECT (SELECT drinker FROM Frequents WHERE frequents.bar='Satisfaction');
select drinker from frequents where bar = 'James Joyce Pub' and drinker IN (select drinker from frequents where bar = 'Satisfaction');
(SELECT drinker FROM Frequents WHERE bar= 'James Joyce Pub') INTERSECT (SELECT drinker FROM Frequents WHERE bar ='Satisfaction');
select drinker from frequents as f where bar = 'James Joyce Pub' and exists (select drinker from frequents where bar='Satisfaction' and drinker=f.drinker);

SELECT x.drinker
	FROM frequents x, frequents y
	WHERE x.drinker = y.drinker
		AND x.bar = 'James Joyce Pub'
		AND y.bar = 'Satisfaction'
;
select drinker from frequents where bar = 'Satisfaction' intersect select drinker from frequents where bar = 'James Joyce Pub';

(SELECT drinker
FROM Frequents
WHERE bar = 'James Joyce Pub')
INTERSECT
(SELECT drinker

WHERE bar = 'Satisfaction');

AND F1.bar = 'James Joyce Pub'
AND F2.bar = 'Satisfaction';

SELECT f.drinker
FROM Frequents f, Frequents g
WHERE f.drinker = g.drinker AND f.bar = 'James Joyce Pub' AND g.bar = 'Satisfaction'
GROUP BY f.drinker;
select drinker from frequents where bar= 'Satisfaction' intersect select drinker from frequents where bar='James Joyce Pub';

select f1.drinker
from frequents f1, frequents f2
where f1.drinker = f2.drinker
and f1.bar = 'James Joyce Pub'
and f2.bar = 'Satisfaction';

(SELECT Frequents.drinker
FROM Frequents
WHERE Frequents.bar = 'James Joyce Pub')
INTERSECT
(SELECT Frequents.drinker
FROM Frequents
WHERE Frequents.bar = 'Satisfaction');

SELECT DISTINCT T.drinker
FROM
  (
    SELECT frequents1.bar AS bar1, frequents2.bar AS bar2, frequents1.drinker AS drinker
    FROM frequents AS frequents1, frequents as frequents2
    WHERE frequents1.drinker=frequents2.drinker
  ) T
WHERE T.bar1 = 'James Joyce Pub' AND T.bar2 = 'Satisfaction';

column1: (select drinker from frequents where bar='Satisfaction') intersect (select drinker from frequents where bar='James Joyce Pub');

SELECT f.drinker
FROM Frequents f,
	(SELECT drinker
	FROM Frequents
	WHERE bar = 'James Joyce Pub') jjp
WHERE bar = 'Satisfaction'
AND jjp.drinker = f.drinker;

(SELECT DISTINCT frequents.drinker
FROM frequents
WHERE frequents.bar = 'James Joyce Pub')
INTERSECT ALL 
(SELECT DISTINCT frequents.drinker 
FROM frequents
WHERE frequents.bar = 'Satisfaction');
